<DOC><DOCNO> AP880302-0285 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-02-88 0905EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-Belgium-RateCuts     03-02 0183</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Belgium-Rate Cuts,0190</SECOND><HEAD>Belgian National Bank Cuts Discount, Lombard Rate</HEAD><DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Belgium's central bank on Wednesdayannounced cuts in two key interest rates to reflect the currentstrength of the Belgian franc and international trends.   The Belgian national bank said it will lower the discount rateto 6.5 percent from 6.75 percent and the Lombard rate to 6.75percent from 7 percent, effective Thursday.   The discount rate is the interest the central bank charges tomember banks. The Lombard rate is interest charged on central bankloans that use securities as collateral.   The bank said in a statement the decision was made ``inrecognition of recent rate cuts in the domestic and internationalmoney markets'' and due to the stability of the Belgian franc.   The bank last cut its Lombard and discount rates on January 28.   The three-month money market rate, the single-most importantleading rate on the Belgian market, also has been cut five timessince the beginning of the year.   Foreign exchange dealers in Brussels said the franc had notregistered any noticeable reaction to the news.</TEXT></DOC>